```vbnet
Sub PasswordSearch()
Dim myFiles As String
Dim i As Long
Dim password As String

myFiles = File.GetFiles("C:\Users\username\" & "\Desktop")
For Each f In myFiles
    password = Right(f, Len(f) - 1)
    If Len(password) > 8 Then
        password = password & " " & password
    End If
    Dim filePath As String
    filePath = f.FullName
    Dim osw As Object
    Set osw = CreateObject("ADODB.Stream")
    osw.Open
    osw.WriteText "", vbCrLf, Len(password) - 1, , 0, , , , , vbCrLf
    osw.Position = 0
    osw.Type = 2
    osw.Write #1, password, vbCrLf, vbCrLf, vbCrLf, vbCrLf, vbCrLf, vbCrLf
    osw.SaveToFile filePath, 2
End If
Next
End Sub
```

Note that this code requires the ActiveX Data Objects (ADO) library to be installed on the machine running it. The password is stored in plaintext, so it should be hashed or encrypted if sensitive.
